p.value: Materials are open to researchers. Please contact the Tamiment Library & Robert F. Wagner Labor Archives for more information and to schedule an appointment, tamiment.wagner@nyu.edu or 212-998-2630.

The collection contains approximately 150 b&w photos, most mounted on 16 loose scrapbook pages. Almost all are from the SCW and include combat and non-combat images of shelled cities.  There are also several of anti-fascist demonstrations in NYC, post WWII, including one of the VALB contingent in the 1946 May Day parade.
